                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-884" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-884" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-884" type="surname" value="FOX"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-884" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH FOX</persName>
                  </hi>. I am single, and live at No. 21, Castle-street, Long-acre. On the 17th of June, the prisoner hired a furnished room of me, and staid till the 8th of September—there was a blanket, seven pillows, two flat</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183709180134"></xptr>
               <p>irons, and other things—when she went out one day, I went into her room and found these things missing, and the feathers taken out of the bed—she was living with a man whom she represented as her husband—these things are mine—(<hi rend="italic">looking at them</hi>.)</p>
               <p>
